# In this example, we take an input u32, and increment it unless it is the maximum value, in which case the value is returned on the error path.
# NOTE: this uses a hack where we have 'u32.type' sort of as dataflow, even though it's within the control flow category!
# This is because we FIRST evaluate & erase type-level values as dataflow during typechecking, THEN the map becomes valid control flow!
# This is very confusing!!
# Val(U32) -> Val(U32) + Val(U32)
